"""Bridge-HRR v5.1 — compositional geometry for two-hop KG reasoning (strict gate).

Result this package reproduces, end to end:

  Held-out two-hop composition on FB15k-237 is NOT recovered by holographic
  memory (any readout), NOR by pure RotatE geometry (which sits at the
  popularity floor). It IS recovered by geometry trained for composition:
  a RotatE atomic objective PLUS a path-consistency objective
  (theta_h + theta_r1 + theta_r2 -> theta_t over observed 2-hops). The
  composed key then generalizes to unseen bridge edges via a single vector
  add + nearest-neighbour -- no memory, no attention, no resonator.

  Path-consistency training installs a SMALL BUT REAL clean-generalization
  signal (strict-gated MRR 0.105 vs 0.082 popularity, 0.022 atomic-only). The
  larger v5 headline was ~half inflated by composites reachable through alternate
  train paths; see RESULTS_v5_1.md. Composition must be paid for in the objective,
  and even then the clean payoff here is modest.
"""
__version__ = "5.1.0"
